# Academic Content Guidelines

## Publication Entry Standards

### Required Fields
- `title`: Use official publication title
- `venue`: Conference/journal name and year (e.g., "ICRA, 2024" or "IEEE Transactions on Robotics, 2023")
- `authors`: List of author keys from [_data/authors.yml](mdc:_data/authors.yml)

### Optional Fields
- `description`: Brief, informative summary (supports markdown)
- `paper`: Direct URL to official paper
- `arxiv`: ArXiv ID (numbers only, URL generated automatically)
- `video`: Link to demonstration video
- `project_page`: Link to dedicated project website
- `github`: GitHub repository URL
- `image`: Preview image path (relative to `images/`)
- `awards`: Special recognition or honors

### Author Management
- Add new collaborators to [_data/authors.yml](mdc:_data/authors.yml) before referencing
- Use consistent author keys across all publications
- Mark yourself with `is_me: true` for highlighting
- Include author websites when available

## Project Documentation
Follow the format in [_data/projects.yml](mdc:_data/projects.yml):
- **Academic projects**: Include course context and technical details
- **Personal projects**: Highlight key technologies and outcomes
- **Awards/Recognition**: Mention prizes, rankings, or special recognition
- **Video links**: Include demonstration videos when available

## Image Standards
- **Aspect ratio**: 1:1 (square format)
- **Minimum size**: 320px width/height
- **Organization**: Create subdirectories in `images/` by project/publication
- **Formats**: Prefer JPG for photos, PNG for graphics/diagrams
- **Mouseover effects**: Include both static image and video/alternate image when applicable

## Writing Style
- **Technical accuracy**: Use precise terminology for research areas
- **Conciseness**: Keep descriptions informative but brief
- **Markdown support**: Use markdown formatting in description fields
- **External links**: Ensure all URLs are current and accessible
- **Consistency**: Maintain consistent formatting across similar content types

## Content Organization
- **Chronological order**: List newest items first in data files
- **Categorization**: Separate publications, projects, awards, and miscellaneous items
- **Cross-references**: Link related projects and publications when appropriate
- **Update frequency**: Keep CV file current with publication updates

## Professional Standards
- **Verification**: Double-check all URLs, dates, and affiliations
- **Attribution**: Properly credit all collaborators and institutions
- **Copyright**: Ensure proper permissions for images and content
- **Professional tone**: Maintain academic writing standards throughout
